description.en: The Machine Learning Test Ontology was built to characterize failures that have been identified during the use of machine learning tools, in particular the TensorFlow tool.

comments.en: An ontology to describe the testing process in Machine Learning tools to describe how failures occur in these systems. Created by Alexandre Locci Martins and Ana Cristina Vierira de Melo.

comment.en: The runtime implements the management of sessions, thread pools, and executors. TensorFlow has a common runtime (core/common runtime) and a distribution runtime (core/distributed runtime). Common runtime supports theexecutions on a local machine, and distribution runtime allows to deploy TensorFlow on distributed ones.

API Acronym for Application Programming Interface. API's . The API's function is to link between different applications serving the user. They enable integration between different systems and make user actions faster with the expected responses. The API always works in the background, so the average user does not even see the API in operation. TensorFlow provides APIs in many programming languages as C, C++, Java, and Python, which one are located in the python, c, cc and java directories.

The goal of TensorFlow Model Analysis is to provide a mechanism for model evaluation in TFX. TensorFlow Model Analysis allows to perform model evaluations in the TFX pipeline, and view resultant metrics and plots in a Jupyter notebook.
